The '''Great Hall of Wootton Major''' was the meeting place of the village [[Wootton Major]] wherein the villagers held meetings, debates, public feasts, and family gatherings. Adjoined to the Great Hall were the Cook's House and the Kitchen, for the [[Master Cook]] was an important person in the village who provided suitable fare for all of the gatherings. It was also the site for the winter festival and [[The Feast of Good Children]].<ref>{{SOWM|Smith}}</ref>
